3436 typedef enum

3447 
3448  // The GBR naming is a reminder the ordering of the hardware input channels is also GRB, not RGB
3449  NTV2_GBRFull_to_YCbCr_Rec709_Matrix, // RGB full range -> YCbCr Rec 709 (HD)
3450  NTV2_GBRFull_to_YCbCr_Rec601_Matrix, // RGB full range -> YCbCr Rec 601 (SD)
3451  NTV2_GBRSMPTE_to_YCbCr_Rec709_Matrix, // RGB SMPTE range -> YCbCr Rec 709 (HD)
3452  NTV2_GBRSMPTE_to_YCbCr_Rec601_Matrix, // RGB SMPTE range -> YCbCr Rec 601 (SD)

3529 // The Mac implementation of color-space conversion uses the two LUT banks for holding
3530 // two separate gamma-conversion LUTs: one for RGB=>YUV and the other for YUV=>RGB. This
3531 // defines which bank is used for which conversion LUT.
3532 // NOTE: using the LUT Banks this way conflicts with using them for AutoCirculate "Color Correction".
3533 #define kLUTBank_RGB2YUV 0 // uses Bank 0 when converting from RGB=>YUV
3534 #define kLUTBank_YUV2RGB 1 // uses Bank 1 when converting from YUV=>RGB
3535 #define kLUTBank_SMPTE2FULL 0 // uses Bank 0 when converting from SMPTE=>Full range RGB
3536 #define kLUTBank_FULL2SMPTE 1 // uses Bank 0 when converting from Full=>SMPTE range RGB
3537

3548  NTV2_LUTGamma18_Rec709, // Translates between Mac 1.8 and Rec 709, Full Range
3549  NTV2_LUTGamma18_Rec601_SMPTE, // Same as NTV2_LUTGamma18_Rec601, SMPTE range
3550  NTV2_LUTGamma18_Rec709_SMPTE, // Same as NTV2_LUTGamma18_Rec709, SMPTE range
